%U A397407 2787593149816327892712625137443617065926656,191561942608236107294793388761536476967410988646137856,210624583337114373395836055367351736009337748096454465434566000640
%N A397407 The number of 2-colorings of the Aztec diamond of order n up to rotation and reflection.
%C A397407 The Aztec diamond of order n has 2*n*(n+1) squares, and we count the colorings up to the eight symmetries of the dihedral group of the square.
%H A397407 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aztec_diamond">Aztec diamond</a>.
%F A397407 When n is even, a(n) = 1/8*(2^(2*n*(n+1)) + 2*2^(n*(n+1)/2) + 3*2^(n*(n+1)) + 2*2^(n*(3+2*n)/2)).
%F A397407 When n is odd, a(n) = 1/8*(2^(2*n*(n+1)) + 2*2^(n*(n+1)/2) + 3*2^(n*(n+1)) + 2*2^((2*n+1)*(n+1)/2)).
%e A397407 One of the a(3) = 2102800 colorings of the order 3 Aztec diamond is the following.
%e A397407       0 1
%e A397407     1 0 1 0
%e A397407   0 1 0 0 1 1
%e A397407   1 1 0 1 0 1
%e A397407     0 1 0 0
%e A397407       0 1
%t A397407 a[n_]:=1/8 (2^(2 n (n + 1)) + 2*2^If[EvenQ[n], (2 n (n + 1) - n)/2 + n, (2 n (n + 1) - (n + 1))/2 + n + 1] + 2*2^(n (n + 1)/2) + 3*2^(n (n + 1)))
%Y A397407 Cf. A054247 (square), A061348 (triangle), A061709 (triangle perimeter), A255016 (torus grid).
